Here's the typical file structure for CGI programs and web server setup:

Basic Web Server Directory Structure
/var/www/
├── html/                           # Document root (static files)
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── style.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── script.js
│   └── images/
│       └── logo.png
├── cgi-bin/                        # CGI scripts directory
│   ├── hello.py                    # Our first CGI script
│   ├── form_handler.py             # Our form handling script
│   ├── data_api.py                 # API endpoint script
│   └── utils/                      # CGI utility modules
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── database.py
│       └── helpers.py
└── logs/                           # Web server logs
    ├── access.log
    └── error.log

Complete Example File Structure
/var/www/
├── html/
│   ├── index.html                  # Main website page
│   ├── contact.html                # Contact form page
│   └── css/
│       └── main.css
├── cgi-bin/
│   ├── contact.py                  # Contact form handler
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── users.py                # User API endpoints
│   │   ├── products.py             # Product API endpoints
│   │   └── auth.py                 # Authentication handler
│   ├── admin/
│   │   ├── dashboard.py            # Admin dashboard
│   │   └── reports.py              # Admin reports
│   └── lib/                        # Shared libraries
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── config.py               # Configuration
│       ├── database.py             # Database operations
│       └── session.py              # Session management
└── data/                           # Data storage
    ├── uploads/                    # File uploads
    ├── cache/                      # Cache files
    └── sessions/                   # Session files


Apache Configuration Structure
/etc/apache2/
├── apache2.conf                    # Main configuration
├── sites-available/
│   ├── 000-default.conf           # Default site
│   └── mysite.conf                 # Custom site config
├── sites-enabled/
│   └── 000-default.conf           # Symlink to enabled site
├── mods-available/
│   └── cgi.load                    # CGI module
├── mods-enabled/
│   └── cgi.load                    # Symlink to enabled module
└── conf-available/
    └── cgi.conf                    # CGI-specific configuration
